         <h1>Statement of User Rights and Responsibilities</h1>
         <p>Savorboard (www.savorboard.com, www.wanerdao.com) and all relative productions are from Savorboard Corporation. This Statement of Rights and Responsibilities ("Statement") derives from the Savorboard Principles, and governs our relationship with users and others who interact with Savorboard. By using or accessing Savorboard, you agree to this Statement.</p>
         <h3>1.	Privacy</h3>
         <p>Your privacy is very important to us. We designed our Privacy Policy to make important disclosures about how you can use Savorboard to share with others and how we collect and can use your content and information.  We encourage you to read the Privacy Policy, and to use it to help make informed decisions.</p>
         <h3>2.	Sharing Your Content and Information</h3>
         <p>Information you provide to us:</p>
         <p>Information About Yourself. When you Sign up for Savorboard you provide us with your name, email, gender, and birth date. During the registration process we give you the opportunity to connect with your friends, schools, and employers. You will also be able to add a picture of yourself. In some cases we may ask for additional information for security reasons or to provide specific services to you. Once you register you can provide other information about yourself by connecting with, for example, your current city, hometown, family, relationships, networks, activities, interests, and places.   You can also provide personal information about yourself, such as your political and religious views.</p>
         <p>During the registration process, we ask for your date of birth to verify whether you are a minor, and so that we can limit your access to content and advertisements that are not age appropriate.  </p>
         <p>Content. One of the primary reasons people use Savorboard is to share content with others. Examples include when you update your status, upload or take a photo, upload or record a video, share a link, create an activity or a group, make a comment, write something on someone’s blog, write a note, or send someone a message. If you do not want us to store metadata associated with content you share on Savorboard (such as photos), please remove the metadata before uploading the content.</p>
